***********************************************************
***                                                     ***
***         AdaBroker : an IDL to Ada compiler          ***
***                                                     ***
***********************************************************

Installation :
--------------
- run make in AdaBroker/omniidl2 to compile omniidl2


Usage :
-------
- omniidl2 -bada myinterface.idl creates several files :

- myinterface.ads, myinterface.adb : these files contain
the mapping for user defined types (client and server side)

- myinterface-impl.ads, myinterface-impl.adb : these files
are to be filled by the user. They contain the implementation
of the server.

- myinterface-proxies.ads, myinterface-proxies.adb : these files
contain utilities to make proxy calls

- myinterface-skeleton.ads, myinterface-skeleton.adb : these files
contain utilities for the server-side implementation.

- myinterface-marshal.ads, marshal-marshal.adb : they contain
subprograms to marshall types according to the GIOP protocol.


